\mt1 Psalms [Praises] 151  
\io1 \it Context: Historically, Psalm 151 is found in the Septuagint, the Greek Old Covenant text, but not in the Hebrew Masoretic text.\it*  
\c 1  
\cd Context: When David [Beloved] fought in one-on-one combat with Goliath [Exposer, Uncovered]. (1 Sam 17:4-11, 17:26, 17:34-37, 17:43-51)  
\b  
\q1
\v 1 I was small among my brothers,  
\q2 and youngest in my father’s house.  
\q2 I tended my father’s sheep.   
\q1
\v 2 My hands formed a musical instrument,  
\q2 and my fingers tuned a lute.   
\q1
\v 3 Who shall tell \tl adonai\tl* ·my Lord·?  
\q2 \sc Adonai\sc* himself, he himself hears.   
\q1
\v 4 He sent forth his angel and took me from my father’s sheep,  
\q2 and he anointed me with his anointing oil.   
\q1
\v 5 My brothers were handsome and tall;  
\q2 but \sc Adonai\sc* did not take pleasure in them.   
\q1
\v 6 I went out to meet the Philistine [To roll in dust (As an insult)],  
\q2 and he cursed me by his idols.   
\q1
\v 7 But I drew his own sword and beheaded him,  
\q2 and removed reproach from the children of Israel [God prevails].   
\b  